# Runtime SQLite databases (per-machine, not portable).
# F-KnowledgeBaseExpansion (v0.55.7.1): the *contents* of data/ are
# ignored at the top level so nothing operator-machine-specific
# (SQLite WAL, agent cache, conductivity logs, parquet bursts) ever
# gets committed by accident. The knowledge subtree is the one
# carve-out — Markdown procedures, manuals, and operator-dropped PDFs
# travel with the repo so a fresh clone has the same RAG corpus the
# demo expects. The exclusion list (data/knowledge/**/*.lance,
# data/knowledge/**/*.cache) still blocks the LanceDB index + any
# embedding cache that could land here later.
data/*
!data/knowledge/
data/knowledge/**/*.lance
data/knowledge/**/*.cache

# Reference curves and predictor model — operator-supplied, not source-controlled
cooldown_v5/

